Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on sequence-to-sequence models for generating captions from video features. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper uses I3D action features to generate captions. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper explores different conditioning methods for the decoder. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with video captioning. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as the paper uses machine learning techniques for generating captions.
